<p>I'm trying to install <code>log.io</code> on <code>Ubuntu 14.04</code>. Everything work fine on terminal with this command</p>  <pre><code>sudo npm install -g log.io --user "ubuntu" </code></pre>  <p>But this does not work inside <code>Ansible</code>.</p>  <p>First I tried to use <code>npm</code> module</p>  <pre><code>npm: name=log.io global=yes </code></pre>  <p>This does not work since log.io tried to create <code>/root/.log.io</code> and it does not have permission</p>  <p>I also tried <code>shell</code> but same</p>  <pre><code>shell: npm install -g log.io --user "ubuntu" sudo: yes </code></pre>  <p>Or </p>  <pre><code>npm: name=log.io global=yes become: yes become_user: ubuntu </code></pre>  <p>Can anyone help me on this? Thanks!</p>